{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885182763,"sessionID":"ses_28502d4deffeN9iJueUE2C5tWU","part":{"id":"prt_d7afe41590015jinw10OqeiLJZ","messageID":"msg_d7afe1407001iuIufcQKtU4jrX","sessionID":"ses_28502d4deffeN9iJueUE2C5tWU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","content":"# AR-020 Design: CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe `pack` command is the foundation of the AgentCube CLI toolchain. It validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Agent Workspace                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Source Files    Metadata    Dependencies    Dockerfile (optional)     │  │\n│  │  (*.py/*.java)   (YAML)      (requirements/  (generated)               │  │\n│  │                              pom.xml)                                  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              Pack Command                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  1. Validate Workspace Structure                                       │  │\n│  │     ├── Check path exists and is directory                             │  │\n│  │     ├── Validate language-specific files                               │  │\n│  │     └── Verify entrypoint detection                                    │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  2. Load/Create Metadata                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Try agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml          │  │\n│  │     ├── Apply CLI option overrides                                     │  │\n│  │     └── Validate with Pydantic (AgentMetadata)                         │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  3. Process Dependencies                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Python: requirements.txt analysis                              │  │\n│  │     └── Java: pom.xml parsing                                          │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  4. Generate Dockerfile (optional)                                     │  │\n│  │     ├── Language-specific template selection                         │  │\n│  │     └── Write to workspace root                                        │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  5. Update Metadata & Report                                           │  │\n│  │     ├── Persist updated metadata                                       │  │\n│  │     └── Display success with paths                                     │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           PackRuntime Flow                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  CLI     │──►│  Pack    │──►│ Validate │──►│  Load    │──►│  Apply   │  │\n│  │  Options │   │  Runtime │   │ Workspace│   │ Metadata │   │ Overrides│  │\n│  └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                      │                                            │        │\n│                      ▼                                            ▼        │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Report  │◀──│  Update  │◀──│ Generate │◀──│ Process  │◀──│ Validate │  │\n│  │  Result  │   │  Metadata│   │ Dockerfile│   │   Deps   │   │ Language │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, `pack` command, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` class implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata` model, `MetadataService` |\n| `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring |\n| `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example Python agent |\n| `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example Java agent |\n\n**Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):\n- `agentcube`\n- `agentcube.cli`\n- `agentcube.runtime`\n- `agentcube.operations`\n- `agentcube.services`\n\n## Console Script Entry Point\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n```\n\nTyper app object:\n```python\napp = typer.Typer(\n    name=\"agentcube\",\n    help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\",\n    no_args_is_help=True,\n    rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n    add_completion=False\n)\n```\n\n## Typer — Root Callback\n\n```python\ndef main(\n    version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n        callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n```\n\nGlobal verbose behavior:\n- When `verbose=True`, calls `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n\n## Typer — `pack` Command\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Command Behavior\n\n1. **Options and Defaults**:\n   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n   - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`)\n   - `language` = `None` (`--language`)\n   - `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`)\n   - `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`)\n   - `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`)\n   - `description` = `None` (`--description`)\n   - `output` = `None` (`--output`)\n   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n\n2. **Successful Pack**:\n   - Uses Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n   - Prints success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path`\n   - Metadata path reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n3. **Pack Failure Handling**:\n   - Calls `_handle_error(e, \"packing agent\", verbose)`\n   - Prints `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n   - If `verbose=True`, prints full traceback\n   - Exits with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n## Helper Functions\n\n### `version_callback`\n\n```python\ndef version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display version and exit.\"\"\"\n    if value:\n        console.print(f\"AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}\")\n        raise typer.Exit()\n```\n\n### `_handle_error`\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Handle command errors with optional traceback.\"\"\"\n    console.print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n## Runtime Classes\n\n### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\nCore class responsible for packaging agent workspaces.\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize PackRuntime with optional verbose logging.\"\"\"\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Main entry point for packaging an agent workspace.\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to the agent workspace directory\n            **options: CLI options and overrides\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict containing packaging results including agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path\n        \"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n#### Core Methods\n\n##### `_validate_workspace_structure`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate that workspace exists and contains required files.\n    \n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If workspace doesn't exist or is not a directory\n    \"\"\"\n    if not workspace_path.exists():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n    if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n```\n\n##### `_load_or_create_metadata`\n\n```python\ndef _load_or_create_metadata(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> AgentMetadata:\n    \"\"\"\n    Load existing metadata or create new from options.\n    \n    Metadata loading precedence:\n    1. agent_metadata.yaml (primary)\n    2. agent.yaml (fallback)\n    3. metadata.yaml (fallback)\n    4. Create new from defaults + options\n    \"\"\"\n    ...\n```\n\n##### `_apply_option_overrides`\n\n```python\ndef _apply_option_overrides(\n    self, \n    metadata: AgentMetadata, \n    options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> AgentMetadata:\n    \"\"\"\n    Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\n    \n    Override precedence (highest first):\n    1. Explicit CLI options\n    2. Existing metadata values\n    3. Default values from AgentMetadata\n    \"\"\"\n    ...\n```\n\n##### `_validate_language_compatibility`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_language_compatibility(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata: AgentMetadata\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate workspace contents match declared language.\n    \n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If language-specific files are missing\n    \"\"\"\n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n```\n\n##### `_validate_python_compatibility`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\n    \n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If no Python files found\n    \"\"\"\n    py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n    if not py_files:\n        raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n```\n\n##### `_validate_java_compatibility`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate Java workspace has pom.xml.\n    \n    Raises:\n        ValueError: If pom.xml not found\n    \"\"\"\n    pom_path = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n    if not pom_path.exists():\n        raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace (required for Java agents)\")\n```\n\n##### `_process_dependencies`\n\n```python\ndef _process_dependencies(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata: AgentMetadata\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Process and validate language-specific dependencies.\n    \"\"\"\n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n```\n\n##### `_process_python_dependencies`\n\n```python\ndef _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Process Python requirements.txt if present.\n    Validates file exists and logs dependency count.\n    \"\"\"\n    req_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n    if req_file.exists():\n        deps = [line.strip() for line in req_file.read_text().splitlines() \n                if line.strip() and not line.startswith(\"#\")]\n        self.logger.info(f\"Found {len(deps)} Python dependencies\")\n```\n\n##### `_process_java_dependencies`\n\n```python\ndef _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Process Java Maven dependencies from pom.xml.\n    \"\"\"\n    import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n    \n    pom_path = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n    if pom_path.exists():\n        try:\n            tree = ET.parse(pom_path)\n            root = tree.getroot()\n            # Count dependency elements\n            deps = root.findall(\".//{http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0}dependency\")\n            self.logger.info(f\"Found {len(deps)} Maven dependencies\")\n        except ET.ParseError as e:\n            self.logger.warning(f\"Could not parse pom.xml: {e}\")\n```\n\n##### `_generate_dockerfile`\n\n```python\ndef _generate_dockerfile(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata: AgentMetadata\n) -> Optional[Path]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Dockerfile based on language and metadata.\n    \n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to agent workspace\n        metadata: Agent metadata with configuration\n        \n    Returns:\n        Path to generated Dockerfile, or None if generation skipped\n    \"\"\"\n    dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n    \n    if metadata.language == \"python\":\n        content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n    elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n        content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n    else:\n        self.logger.warning(f\"Unsupported language for Dockerfile generation: {metadata.language}\")\n        return None\n    \n    dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n    self.logger.info(f\"Generated Dockerfile at {dockerfile_path}\")\n    return dockerfile_path\n```\n\n##### `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n\n```python\ndef _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Python-specific Dockerfile content.\n    \n    Template includes:\n    - Python 3.11 slim base image\n    - Working directory setup\n    - Requirements installation\n    - Source code copying\n    - Entrypoint configuration\n    - Port exposure\n    \"\"\"\n    entrypoint = metadata.entrypoint or \"python main.py\"\n    port = metadata.port or 8080\n    \n    return f'''FROM python:3.11-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install dependencies\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\n# Copy source code\nCOPY . .\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE {port}\n\n# Run the agent\nCMD [\"{entrypoint}\"]\n'''\n```\n\n##### `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n\n```python\ndef _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Java-specific Dockerfile content.\n    \n    Template includes:\n    - Maven build stage\n    - JAR extraction\n    - Runtime stage with minimal base\n    - Port exposure\n    \"\"\"\n    port = metadata.port or 8080\n    \n    return f'''# Build stage\nFROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17-alpine AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY pom.xml .\nCOPY src ./src\n\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n\n# Runtime stage\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy built JAR\nCOPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE {port}\n\n# Run the agent\nENTRYPOINT [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"app.jar\"]\n'''\n```\n\n##### `_update_pack_metadata`\n\n```python\ndef _update_pack_metadata(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata: AgentMetadata, \n    dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Update metadata with pack results.\n    \n    Sets:\n    - pack_timestamp: Current UTC time\n    - dockerfile_generated: Whether Dockerfile was created\n    \"\"\"\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\n    \n    metadata.pack_timestamp = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n    metadata.dockerfile_generated = dockerfile_path is not None\n    \n    self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n```\n\n##### `_prepare_output_path`\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_output_path(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    output_path: Optional[str]\n) -> Path:\n    \"\"\"\n    Resolve output path for packaged workspace.\n    \n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Source workspace path\n        output_path: Optional explicit output path\n        \n    Returns:\n        Resolved output path\n    \"\"\"\n    if output_path:\n        return Path(output_path)\n    return workspace_path\n```\n\n##### `_infer_entrypoint`\n\n```python\ndef _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Attempt to infer entrypoint from workspace contents.\n    \n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to workspace\n        language: Programming language\n        \n    Returns:\n        Inferred entrypoint command\n    \"\"\"\n    if language == \"python\":\n        # Look for main.py, app.py, or any .py file\n        for candidate in [\"main.py\", \"app.py\", \"agent.py\"]:\n            if (workspace_path / candidate).exists():\n                return f\"python {candidate}\"\n        # Fallback to first .py file\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if py_files:\n            return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n        return \"python main.py\"\n    \n    elif language == \"java\":\n        # For Java, entrypoint is typically the JAR\n        return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n    \n    return \"\"\n```\n\n## Service Classes\n\n### `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\nService for loading, saving, and validating agent metadata.\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"\n        Load metadata from workspace.\n        \n        Loading precedence:\n        1. agent_metadata.yaml\n        2. agent.yaml\n        3. metadata.yaml\n        \n        Raises:\n            FileNotFoundError: If no metadata file exists\n        \"\"\"\n        for filename in [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]:\n            filepath = workspace_path / filename\n            if filepath.exists():\n                data = yaml.safe_load(filepath.read_text())\n                return AgentMetadata.model_validate(data)\n        \n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}\")\n\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"\n        Save metadata to workspace.\n        \n        Always writes to agent_metadata.yaml with:\n        - default_flow_style=False\n        - indent=2\n        - sort_keys=False\n        - exclude_none=True\n        \"\"\"\n        filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n        yaml.dump(data, filepath.open(\"w\"), \n                  default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n\n    def update_metadata(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        updates: Dict[str, Any]\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load, update, and save metadata.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        for key, value in updates.items():\n            setattr(metadata, key, value)\n        self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        return metadata\n\n    def validate_workspace(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        metadata: AgentMetadata\n    ) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace contents match metadata.\"\"\"\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        return True\n\n    def _validate_python_workspace(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        metadata: AgentMetadata\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Python-specific validation.\"\"\"\n        if not list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\")):\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n\n    def _validate_java_workspace(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        metadata: AgentMetadata\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Java-specific validation.\"\"\"\n        if not (workspace_path / \"pom.xml\").exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")\n```\n\n## Data Models\n\n### `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n\nCore metadata model for agent configuration.\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n| `pack_timestamp` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | ISO timestamp of pack operation |\n| `dockerfile_generated` | `Optional[bool]` | `None` | Whether Dockerfile was generated |\n\n#### Validators\n\n```python\n@field_validator(\"language\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Validate and normalize language.\"\"\"\n    v = v.lower()\n    if v not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n    return v\n\n@field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Validate and normalize build_mode.\"\"\"\n    v = v.lower()\n    if v not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n    return v\n\n@field_validator(\"port\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Validate port number.\"\"\"\n    if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Invalid port: {v}. Must be between 1 and 65535\")\n    return v\n```\n\n### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\nDataclass for CLI option packaging.\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override agent name |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` | Language override |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Entrypoint override |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | Port override |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` | Build mode override |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Requirements file path |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Description override |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Workload manager URL |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Router URL |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Readiness probe path |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | Readiness probe port |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Agent endpoint |\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"Options for metadata creation/overrides during pack.\"\"\"\n    \n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from dict, filtering None values.\"\"\"\n        filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None}\n        return cls(**filtered)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required Dependencies (`pyproject.toml`)\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n### Optional Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n```\n\n## Module Exports\n\n### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n\n```python\n\"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n\n__version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n\nfrom agentcube.cli.main import app\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"app\",\n    \"PackRuntime\",\n    \"BuildRuntime\", \n    \"PublishRuntime\",\n    \"InvokeRuntime\",\n]\n```\n\n### `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n\n```python\n\"\"\"Runtime modules for agent lifecycle operations.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"PackRuntime\",\n    \"BuildRuntime\",\n    \"PublishRuntime\",\n    \"InvokeRuntime\",\n    \"StatusRuntime\",\n    \"MetadataOptions\",\n]\n```\n\n## Workflow Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Pack Command Execution Flow                           │\n│                                                                              │\n│  User Input                                                                  │\n│     │                                                                        │\n│     ▼                                                                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐                                                            │\n│  │ agentcube    │                                                            │\n│  │ pack -f .    │                                                            │\n│  │ --agent-name │                                                            │\n│  │ my-agent     │                                                            │\n│  └──────┬───────┘                                                            │\n│         │                                                                    │\n│         ▼                                                                    │\n│  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n│  │   Parse      │────►│   Create     │────►│   Validate   │                 │\n│  │   Options    │     │   PackRuntime│     │   Workspace  │                 │\n│  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────┬───────┘                 │\n│                                                   │                         │\n│                    ┌──────────────────────────────┘                         │\n│                    │                                                         │\n│                    ▼                                                         │\n│  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n│  │   Apply      │◄────│    Load      │◄────│   Process    │                 │\n│  │   Overrides  │     │   Metadata   │     │     Deps     │                 │\n│  └──────┬───────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘                 │\n│         │                                                                    │\n│         ▼                                                                    │\n│  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐                 │\n│  │   Generate   │────►│   Update     │────►│   Display    │                 │\n│  │   Dockerfile │     │   Metadata   │     │   Result     │                 │\n│  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘                 │\n│                                                   │                          │\n│                                                   ▼                          │\n│                                          ┌──────────────┐                   │\n│                                          │   Success    │                   │\n│                                          │   Message    │                   │\n│                                          └──────────────┘                   │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n├── ValueError (validation errors)\n│   ├── Workspace not found\n│   ├── No Python files\n│   ├── No pom.xml\n│   └── Invalid metadata\n├── FileNotFoundError (missing files)\n│   └── Metadata file not found\n└── RuntimeError (runtime failures)\n    └── Pack operation failed\n```\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Message |\n|----------|------------|---------|\n| Missing workspace | ValueError | \"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\" |\n| Not a directory | ValueError | \"Workspace path is not a directory: {path}\" |\n| No Python files | ValueError | \"No Python files found in workspace\" |\n| No pom.xml | ValueError | \"No pom.xml found in workspace (required for Java agents)\" |\n| Invalid language | ValueError | \"Unsupported language: {lang}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\" |\n| Invalid port | ValueError | \"Invalid port: {port}. Must be between 1 and 65535\" |\n| Invalid build_mode | ValueError | \"Unsupported build_mode: {mode}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\" |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Metadata Loading**: The system uses a cascading fallback for metadata files:\n   - Primary: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n   - Fallback 1: `agent.yaml`\n   - Fallback 2: `metadata.yaml`\n   - Creates new metadata if none found\n\n2. **Dockerfile Generation**: Generated Dockerfiles follow language-specific best practices:\n   - Python: Uses slim base, proper layer caching\n   - Java: Multi-stage build with Maven and JRE\n\n3. **Verbose Logging**: When enabled, provides detailed insight into:\n   - File discovery\n   - Dependency processing\n   - Metadata transformations\n   - Validation results\n\n4. **CLI Override Precedence**: Options provided via CLI take precedence over existing metadata values\n\n5. **Rich Progress**: Uses Rich library for beautiful progress indicators during long operations\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775885182720,"end":1775885182759}}}}
