{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885196876,"sessionID":"ses_28502d4deffeN9iJueUE2C5tWU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0195810015VFqHjgfHLiGDM","messageID":"msg_d7b016760001eT2IxmuSyaGNO4","sessionID":"ses_28502d4deffeN9iJueUE2C5tWU","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"wc -l /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md && head -50 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","description":"Verify design.md file"},"output":"961 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md\n# AR-020 Design: CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe `pack` command is the foundation of the AgentCube CLI toolchain. It validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Agent Workspace                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Source Files    Metadata    Dependencies    Dockerfile (optional)     │  │\n│  │  (*.py/*.java)   (YAML)      (requirements/  (generated)               │  │\n│  │                              pom.xml)                                  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              Pack Command                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  1. Validate Workspace Structure                                       │  │\n│  │     ├── Check path exists and is directory                             │  │\n│  │     ├── Validate language-specific files                               │  │\n│  │     └── Verify entrypoint detection                                    │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  2. Load/Create Metadata                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Try agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml          │  │\n│  │     ├── Apply CLI option overrides                                     │  │\n│  │     └── Validate with Pydantic (AgentMetadata)                         │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  3. Process Dependencies                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Python: requirements.txt analysis                              │  │\n│  │     └── Java: pom.xml parsing                                          │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  4. Generate Dockerfile (optional)                                     │  │\n│  │     ├── Language-specific template selection                         │  │\n│  │     └── Write to workspace root                                        │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  5. Update Metadata & Report                                           │  │\n│  │     ├── Persist updated metadata                                       │  │\n│  │     └── Display success with paths                                     │  │\n","metadata":{"output":"961 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/design.md\n# AR-020 Design: CLI pack 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe `pack` command is the foundation of the AgentCube CLI toolchain. It validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Agent Workspace                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Source Files    Metadata    Dependencies    Dockerfile (optional)     │  │\n│  │  (*.py/*.java)   (YAML)      (requirements/  (generated)               │  │\n│  │                              pom.xml)                                  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              Pack Command                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  1. Validate Workspace Structure                                       │  │\n│  │     ├── Check path exists and is directory                             │  │\n│  │     ├── Validate language-specific files                               │  │\n│  │     └── Verify entrypoint detection                                    │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  2. Load/Create Metadata                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Try agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml          │  │\n│  │     ├── Apply CLI option overrides                                     │  │\n│  │     └── Validate with Pydantic (AgentMetadata)                         │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  3. Process Dependencies                                               │  │\n│  │     ├── Python: requirements.txt analysis                              │  │\n│  │     └── Java: pom.xml parsing                                          │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  4. Generate Dockerfile (optional)                                     │  │\n│  │     ├── Language-specific template selection                         │  │\n│  │     └── Write to workspace root                                        │  │\n│  │                                                                        │  │\n│  │  5. Update Metadata & Report                                           │  │\n│  │     ├── Persist updated metadata                                       │  │\n│  │     └── Display success with paths                                     │  │\n","exit":0,"description":"Verify design.md file","truncated":false},"title":"Verify design.md file","time":{"start":1775885196853,"end":1775885196872}}}}
